    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: TREK-1 KO depolarizes membrane potential and increases input resistance of hippocampal pyramidal neurons.\nFigure 2: TREK-1 KO increases the excitability of CA1 pyramidal neurons.\nFigure 3: TREK-1 null alters dendritic sprouting and the number of spines\nFigure 4: TREK-1 KO increases excitatory and inhibitory synaptic transmission in CA1 pyramidal neurons.\nFigure 5: TREK-1 KO increases Functional Expression of Postsynaptic AMPA Receptors.\n\nDnyanada 11/06/2021: The enhanced functional expression of postsynaptic AMPA receptors is inferred from AMPA-EPSC electrophysiological measurements. This paper does not further investigate this phenotype (eg via immunocytochemistry of surface AMPAR) and hence the general term \"postsynaptic process...\" was used.. Experimental description: TREK-1 gene (Kcnk2) knockout (TREK-1 KO) mice were generated on a mixed background of C57BL6J and SV129 strains. Prior to this study, this TREK-1 KO line has been backcrossed with C57BL6J for more than ten generations in our laboratory.",
